01:15:15.150 --> 01:15:17.642
It's good to be home. I know that much.

01:15:18.070 --> 01:15:22.233
I wasn't talking to you, Deeds.
I was talking to that squirrel over there.

01:15:24.201 --> 01:15:26.573
Although it's a shame
about that Cedar fellow...

01:15:26.662 --> 01:15:30.161
...tearing apart your uncle's company
and firing all those nice people.

01:15:30.249 --> 01:15:31.280
Where'd you hear that?

01:15:31.375 --> 01:15:33.948
I watch the stock market channel
all the time.

01:15:34.044 --> 01:15:38.125
I watch because I suspect that anchorman
of being an evil leprechaun.

01:15:38.215 --> 01:15:40.676
He can bullshit everybody else,
but he ain't fooling me.

01:15:40.676 --> 01:15:41.423
He can bullshit everybody else,
but he ain't fooling me.

01:15:45.431 --> 01:15:46.759
There it is.

01:15:56.275 --> 01:15:57.270
Someone!

01:15:57.693 --> 01:15:58.772
Help!

01:16:04.575 --> 01:16:06.449
Deeds! Help!

01:16:07.995 --> 01:16:10.118
Deeds! Help!

01:16:10.206 --> 01:16:11.914
Oh, God! Deeds!

01:16:23.135 --> 01:16:24.463
Oh, my God!

01:16:33.604 --> 01:16:36.142
Where do you got the camera hidden,
in the woods?

01:16:36.232 --> 01:16:37.394
No camera.

01:16:37.483 --> 01:16:39.974
I'm so cold. Please!

01:16:40.235 --> 01:16:42.359
You gonna get mugged in there, too?

01:16:42.446 --> 01:16:43.644
I'm so...

01:16:44.656 --> 01:16:45.736
...sorry.

01:16:45.824 --> 01:16:48.825
I really love you.

01:16:49.870 --> 01:16:51.199
Bullshit!

01:17:16.897 --> 01:17:18.060
I'm coming!

01:17:20.526 --> 01:17:23.195
Go down! Go down!

01:17:23.278 --> 01:17:25.187
Here comes the black foot.

01:17:27.199 --> 01:17:28.195
No!

01:17:31.912 --> 01:17:34.201
I know it's gross, but grab it.

01:17:38.794 --> 01:17:40.917
I got you. I got you.

01:17:41.088 --> 01:17:45.797
-Oh, God, your foot is disgusting!
-I know, I know. Come here.

01:17:46.427 --> 01:17:49.048
Come on, you okay? You okay?

01:17:49.597 --> 01:17:50.841
I think so.

01:17:54.518 --> 01:17:57.602
You didn't really fall out of an apple tree,
did you?

01:17:59.356 --> 01:18:00.352
No.

01:18:02.985 --> 01:18:04.609
But I really love you.

01:18:06.613 --> 01:18:08.736
I don't even know who you are.

01:18:09.825 --> 01:18:11.105
I'm sorry.

01:18:37.687 --> 01:18:39.513
I am so sorry.

01:18:47.530 --> 01:18:51.942
A company in tatters. Preston Blake's
great legacy gone to the highest bidder.

01:18:52.034 --> 01:18:55.984
The shocking announcement from Chuck
Cedar today confirmed that Blake Media...

01:18:56.080 --> 01:18:58.950
...will be stripped down
and sold off piece by piece.

01:18:59.041 --> 01:19:02.457
The only man who could stand up
to Mr. Cedar and save the company...

01:19:02.544 --> 01:19:07.087
...Longfellow Deeds, has apparently
given up his voting rights and left the city.

01:19:07.591 --> 01:19:10.260
The sale's expected to pass
with unanimous consent...

01:19:10.344 --> 01:19:14.556
...at the annual stockholders' meeting
here in New York tomorrow afternoon.

01:19:14.724 --> 01:19:18.306
Sources indicate that virtually
all of Blake's 50, 000 employees...

01:19:18.394 --> 01:19:20.850
...are likely to lose their jobs.

01:19:20.938 --> 01:19:23.263
Wait a minute. I'm a Blake employee.

01:19:23.732 --> 01:19:26.520
Holy shit! This sucks.

01:19:27.611 --> 01:19:31.395
Ladies and gentlemen,
the bottom line is that this divestiture...

01:19:31.490 --> 01:19:36.484
...will result in every shareholder,
all of you and myself included...

01:19:36.912 --> 01:19:39.866
...getting a substantial premium
for our shares.

01:19:41.708 --> 01:19:45.327
But before we vote, the company bylaws
require me to open the floor...

01:19:45.421 --> 01:19:49.501
...to shareholders for statements
either for or against this buyout plan.

01:19:49.592 --> 01:19:51.917
Does anyone wish to make a statement?

01:19:52.178 --> 01:19:55.760
Dismantling this company
would be an insult to a great man.

01:19:56.599 --> 01:19:57.844
You scared me.

01:19:58.100 --> 01:20:02.264
It is an unspeakable outrage
and it cannot be allowed to happen.

01:20:06.108 --> 01:20:08.266
Excuse me. I got a statement.

01:20:11.072 --> 01:20:12.614
Longfellow Deeds.

01:20:12.698 --> 01:20:15.616
Unfortunately, since you sold me
your 300 million shares...

01:20:15.701 --> 01:20:19.201
-...you've no right to speak at this meeting.
-Unfortunately for you...

01:20:19.288 --> 01:20:22.040
...I bought one share of Blake Media
this morning.

01:20:22.124 --> 01:20:25.160
You told me every stockholder
has a say in this company.

01:20:25.252 --> 01:20:26.794
Even the little guy.

01:20:29.131 --> 01:20:33.544
You have two minutes, but remember,
I control 49 percent of this company.

01:20:33.635 --> 01:20:36.720
You're gonna have to persuade
just about everyone else...

01:20:36.805 --> 01:20:38.549
...to start hating money.

01:20:46.106 --> 01:20:48.313
Hello, everybody. I'm Deeds.

01:20:49.192 --> 01:20:52.312
For a little while,
I was a big part of this company.

01:20:52.905 --> 01:20:55.146
I was wicked rich and powerful.

01:20:55.949 --> 01:20:58.654
Now being rich and powerful
isn't a bad thing.

01:20:59.829 --> 01:21:04.075
It looks like the Monopoly guy over there
is pretty darned psyched about it.

01:21:04.791 --> 01:21:07.793
But the problem is
what can happen when you decide...

01:21:07.878 --> 01:21:12.255
...that you would do absolutely anything
to become rich and powerful.

01:21:12.341 --> 01:21:15.176
I don't know who licked the red off
your lollipop today...

01:21:15.260 --> 01:21:17.834
...but you are preaching to the wrong choir.

01:21:17.930 --> 01:21:20.088
All I'm saying is, when you were kids...

01:21:20.182 --> 01:21:23.551
...did you dream
about becoming a savvy investor one day...

01:21:23.644 --> 01:21:26.847
...who would think with his wallet
instead of his heart?

01:21:27.690 --> 01:21:29.517
Come on, I know I didn't.

01:21:30.025 --> 01:21:31.769
I wanted to be a fireman.

01:21:32.569 --> 01:21:36.270
I wanted to be the guy everybody called on
if they were in trouble.

01:21:36.365 --> 01:21:37.943
I wanted to help people...

01:21:38.034 --> 01:21:41.616
...and yeah, I wanted to slide down
those wicked awesome poles.

01:21:42.538 --> 01:21:45.954
But money,
that was the last thing I thought about.

01:21:46.917 --> 01:21:50.001
What about you, sir?
Did you want to be a fireman?

01:21:50.087 --> 01:21:51.416
No, I did not.

01:21:52.965 --> 01:21:55.207
Truth be told, I wanted to be a veterinarian.

01:21:55.301 --> 01:21:57.756
Cool. Why would you want to do that?

01:21:58.637 --> 01:22:01.757
-I wanted to help sick animals.
-And what do you do now?

01:22:01.849 --> 01:22:04.007
I own a chain of slaughterhouses.

01:22:04.268 --> 01:22:07.435
You kind of went the other way
on that one, didn't you?

01:22:08.230 --> 01:22:09.096
Okay.

01:22:09.189 --> 01:22:11.763
In the back. Come on.
Tell me what you wanted to be.

01:22:11.859 --> 01:22:14.065
I wanted to be a magician.

01:22:15.696 --> 01:22:19.741
-And what do you do now?
-I operate a pornographic website.

01:22:20.451 --> 01:22:24.531
That makes people happy also, I guess.
But kind of in a grosser way.

01:22:25.831 --> 01:22:28.156
-Who else?
-I wanted to be a senator.

01:22:28.667 --> 01:22:32.535
-I wanted to be a florist.
-lnternational House Pancake.

01:22:33.046 --> 01:22:34.707
I wanted to be a man.

01:22:36.884 --> 01:22:38.710
That explains a lot.

01:22:39.303 --> 01:22:41.544
I wanted to be a Ping-Pong champion.

01:22:44.391 --> 01:22:47.511
But you're not those things
you wanted to be, are you?

01:22:47.728 --> 01:22:51.512
Everybody made a compromise,
then another compromise, and now...

01:22:51.607 --> 01:22:56.518
...you're about to put 50, 000 people out
of work to make a quick buck? Come on.

01:22:56.821 --> 01:23:00.355
I bet if we ran into the 6th-grade versions
of ourselves right now...

01:23:00.449 --> 01:23:03.485
...they would kick our asses
and put Bubble Yum in our hair...

01:23:03.577 --> 01:23:05.949
...for even thinking about doing this.

01:23:07.915 --> 01:23:10.666
He's right.
I would've beat my greedy ass red.

01:23:10.751 --> 01:23:13.076
I would've thrown myself
off the merry-go-round.

01:23:13.170 --> 01:23:17.631
I would've tied myself naked to a chair
and burned myself with lit cigarettes.

01:23:19.093 --> 01:23:22.010
Did anyone here dream
of becoming a psychiatrist?

01:23:22.137 --> 01:23:23.596
Just kidding, pal.

01:23:24.306 --> 01:23:27.093
There's still hope
for the kids inside of all of us.

01:23:27.184 --> 01:23:29.722
Please don't break up my uncle's company.

01:23:32.022 --> 01:23:33.849
I always wanted to do that.

01:23:44.493 --> 01:23:45.489
Well...

01:23:46.579 --> 01:23:48.080
...that was very touching, Deeds.

01:23:48.080 --> 01:23:48.744
...that was very touching, Deeds.

01:23:49.540 --> 01:23:52.291
It appears this divestiture
has been defeated.

01:23:52.459 --> 01:23:54.535
Unless I'm forgetting something.

01:23:55.796 --> 01:23:57.374
My 300 million votes...

01:23:57.464 --> 01:24:01.378
...plus the 5 million votes I control
as proxy for the foreign investors.

01:24:01.469 --> 01:24:04.006
So which way should I vote my 51 percent?

01:24:05.389 --> 01:24:06.634
I vote aye.

01:24:07.058 --> 01:24:09.264
305 million times.

01:24:10.561 --> 01:24:14.310
The ayes have it.
And Blake Media is no more.

01:24:14.398 --> 01:24:16.189
Not so fast, Chuck.

01:24:17.610 --> 01:24:20.895
Too bad for you, when I was a kid,
I wanted to be a good reporter.

01:24:20.988 --> 01:24:23.740
Miss Bennett,
I wasn't aware you were a stockholder.

01:24:23.824 --> 01:24:25.947
There's a couple things you're not aware of.

01:24:26.034 --> 01:24:28.572
How to tweeze your eyebrows, for instance.

01:24:29.080 --> 01:24:33.623
Also, when Deeds gave away his fortune,
he gave away something that wasn't his.

01:24:35.043 --> 01:24:39.504
-What are you talking about?
-I have here the diary of Preston Blake.

01:24:42.384 --> 01:24:43.795
I stole it and read it.

01:24:43.886 --> 01:24:47.468
Please don't be mad at me.
I did it for good reasons, I promise.

01:24:47.556 --> 01:24:50.723
I would like to read a passage
from Mr. Blake's diary...

01:24:50.810 --> 01:24:53.348
...dated April 12, 1957.

01:24:54.354 --> 01:24:56.644
"I am a volcano of lust.

01:24:56.774 --> 01:25:00.522
"I've gotten this far in business
by following my heart.

01:25:01.028 --> 01:25:02.937
"And I must follow it now...

01:25:03.364 --> 01:25:04.692
"...in love.

01:25:06.408 --> 01:25:09.860
"If she just gives me a sign, an opening."

01:25:10.246 --> 01:25:13.531
Want me to wipe the leaves
on your ficus tree, Mr. Blake?

01:25:14.708 --> 01:25:16.452
You can call me Preston.

01:25:18.504 --> 01:25:22.204
Want me to wipe the leaves
on your ficus tree, Preston?

01:25:23.884 --> 01:25:24.880
Yes.

01:25:27.054 --> 01:25:28.050
Yes.

01:25:28.931 --> 01:25:29.927
Yes!

01:25:31.142 --> 01:25:33.050
Who was this mystery woman?

01:25:33.269 --> 01:25:37.895
I have here the Blake Media ledger
sign-in book from April, 1957.

01:25:38.565 --> 01:25:43.643
On the night of the 12th, there was
only one woman working on Blake's floor.

01:25:44.071 --> 01:25:48.567
Sadly, nine months later, she died,
giving birth to a son.

01:25:49.118 --> 01:25:50.612
A son born...

01:25:50.911 --> 01:25:53.829
...January 23, 1958.

01:25:54.582 --> 01:25:56.124
That is my birthday.

01:25:56.250 --> 01:25:58.408
To Miss Consuela Lopez.

01:25:59.002 --> 01:26:00.414
That is my mother.

01:26:00.587 --> 01:26:03.423
And the rightful heir to $40 billion!

01:26:03.841 --> 01:26:05.335
That is my money?

01:26:05.551 --> 01:26:08.006
A simple DNA test will show...

01:26:08.137 --> 01:26:12.217
...that Emilio Lopez is
the majority stockholder to Blake Media.

01:26:12.433 --> 01:26:14.591
-lt is my money!
-That's your money!

01:26:14.769 --> 01:26:16.263
That is my money!

01:26:17.896 --> 01:26:19.355
Way to go, Emilio!

01:26:19.565 --> 01:26:21.937
I will do good things for everyone.

01:26:22.317 --> 01:26:24.560
Free flamenco lessons for all.

01:26:24.653 --> 01:26:26.729
People, people! Please!

01:26:26.906 --> 01:26:30.405
-That is my money.
-Don't be misled. These are all lies.

01:26:30.701 --> 01:26:31.981
Mr. Cedar...

01:26:32.786 --> 01:26:34.197
...you are fired.

01:26:34.413 --> 01:26:36.156
You can't fire me!

01:26:36.749 --> 01:26:38.208
I'm in control!

01:26:38.583 --> 01:26:40.162
Get your hands off me! I'm Chuck Cedar!

01:26:40.752 --> 01:26:42.496
At the lake, when you saved my life...

01:26:42.588 --> 01:26:45.458
...which I never got a chance
to properly thank you for...

01:26:45.549 --> 01:26:48.041
-You're welcome.
-You said you didn't know who I was.

01:26:48.135 --> 01:26:50.708
And it made me realize
I don't know who I am.

01:26:50.805 --> 01:26:54.090
So I started working on it
and here's what I got so far.

01:26:54.600 --> 01:26:58.051
My name is Babe Bennett.
I grew up in Syossett, Long Island.

01:26:58.187 --> 01:27:02.231
I have brown eyes and I don't know
what my natural hair colour is anymore.

01:27:02.608 --> 01:27:05.728
When I was in 5th grade,
I got a crush on Walter Cronkite.

01:27:05.819 --> 01:27:09.438
I really did have that Holly Hobby notebook
I was telling you about.

01:27:09.532 --> 01:27:13.612
I love Bruce Springsteen, Almond Roca
and Abbott and Costello movies.

01:27:13.828 --> 01:27:16.034
I don't like liquorice or my ankles.

01:27:16.455 --> 01:27:19.622
More importantly,
I know that I messed up real bad.

01:27:19.791 --> 01:27:22.792
And I'd be willing to spend
the rest of my life...

01:27:22.878 --> 01:27:25.250
...begging you to give me another chance...

01:27:25.339 --> 01:27:28.043
...because I am so deeply in love with you...

01:27:28.759 --> 01:27:32.175
...and I know it's definitely
that forever kind of love...

01:27:32.262 --> 01:27:33.591
You're crazy.

01:27:36.016 --> 01:27:37.808
You have beautiful ankles.

01:27:48.070 --> 01:27:49.529
Let's go home.

01:27:51.990 --> 01:27:54.742
You're fired! You! You!

01:27:55.036 --> 01:27:57.526
Oh, you, sir. You are definitely fired.

01:27:58.164 --> 01:28:03.205
I'd like to stay. I think I can really do
some good if I just got another chance.

01:28:06.922 --> 01:28:10.967
Not fired. But tomorrow morning,
you let me change your socks.

01:28:12.595 --> 01:28:13.590
Okay.

01:28:14.889 --> 01:28:18.008
And you, Long-Long-Longfellow...

01:28:18.267 --> 01:28:21.552
...you are the one
who made all this possible...

01:28:21.645 --> 01:28:24.812
...with your beautiful words
and your beautiful spirit.

01:28:24.982 --> 01:28:27.769
And Miss Bennett,
with her beautiful research.

01:28:28.319 --> 01:28:29.861
How can I thank you?

01:28:30.154 --> 01:28:33.439
All I want is your friendship, Emilio.
You're a good man.

01:28:34.575 --> 01:28:35.773
I'll miss you.

01:28:37.077 --> 01:28:38.073
Deeds!

01:28:39.496 --> 01:28:42.332
-How about $1 billion?
-All right.

01:28:42.875 --> 01:28:43.788
Done.

01:28:56.638 --> 01:28:57.718
Holy Jeez!

01:28:58.516 --> 01:28:59.974
I can't believe it!

01:29:00.559 --> 01:29:03.015
-What's that?
-A letter from Hallmark.

01:29:03.104 --> 01:29:05.595
They're actually going to buy
one of my cards.

01:29:05.689 --> 01:29:09.770
-My gosh! Which one?
-The one I wrote for you, remember it?

01:29:10.319 --> 01:29:11.729
Do I remember?

01:29:12.404 --> 01:29:15.240
"Hard to breathe, feels like floating

01:29:15.741 --> 01:29:18.362
"So full of love my heart's exploding

01:29:18.619 --> 01:29:21.655
"Mouth is dry, hands are shaking

01:29:22.081 --> 01:29:24.370
"My heart is yours for the taking

01:29:24.833 --> 01:29:27.123
"Acting weird, not myself

01:29:27.586 --> 01:29:30.208
"Dancing around like the Keebler elf

01:29:30.505 --> 01:29:33.590
"Finally time for this poor schlub

01:29:35.010 --> 01:29:38.177
"To know how it feels to fall in lub"

01:29:38.764 --> 01:29:40.306
I'm so proud of you!

01:29:46.146 --> 01:29:48.898
Can you believe Deeds bought us all these?

01:29:53.487 --> 01:29:55.396
Damn, these things are fast!

01:29:59.701 --> 01:30:00.982
I'm okay!

01:30:02.037 --> 01:30:03.117
I'm okay!

